cancelDispute().details: This function allows anyone to send a cancellation request

completeDispute().details: This function allows anyone to send a completion request

getBuyerResponse(uint256).details: This function returns the buyer's response stored at the specified index

returns._0: response The buyer's response at the provided challenge number

getLatestBuyerResponse().details: This function returns the buyer's response stored at the index      returned by `getChall()`

giveOpinion(bool).details: This function allows the vendor to agree or disagree with the      buyer's response

params._vendorAgrees: True if the vendor agrees with the buyer's latest      response

respondChallenge(bytes32).details: Allows the buyer to respond to the challenge

params._response: The buyer's response to the challenge

submitCommitment(bytes[2],uint256,uint25.details: This function allows the vendor to submit a commitment along with      necessary data for evaluation and proof verification

params._gate: The gate with format [op, s_1, ..., s_a] where the s_i are      the indices of the gate's sons
params._gateNum: The number of the gate being evaluated
params._values: The gate's sons' values. E.g _values[i] = evaluate(s_i)

submitCommitmentLeft(bytes[2],uint256,ui.details: This function allows the vendor to submit a commitment along with      necessary data for evaluation and proof verification

params._gate: The gate with format [op, s_1, ..., s_a] where the s_i are      the indices of the gate's sons
params._gateNum: The number of the gate being evaluated
params._values: The gate's sons' values. E.g _values[i] = evaluate(s_i)

submitCommitmentRight(bytes32[][]).details: This function allows the vendor to submit a commitment along with      necessary data for evaluation and proof verification

params._proof: The proof pi used in the verification

timeoutHasPassed().details: Returns true if the current time is greater or equal to the next      timeout time

returns._0: hasPassed Whether the timeout time has passed

cancelDispute().notice: Send a cancellation request. It will be accepted in any case if      the vendor does this request or if the contract's state is Cancel.      In the case where the contract is waiting for the vendor's opinion      and the timeout has passed, this request will also be accepted.      Otherwise, it will be refused and the transaction reverted.

completeDispute().notice: Send a completion request. It will be accepted in any case if      the buyer does this request or if the contract is complete. In the      case where the contract is waiting for the buyer to respond and the      timeout has passed, this request will also be accepted. Otherwise,      it will be refused and the transaction reverted.

getBuyerResponse(uint256).notice: Get the buyer's response for a specific challenge number

getLatestBuyerResponse().notice: Get the buyer's response to the latest challenge

giveOpinion(bool).notice: Provide an opinion on the buyer's latest response which can be      retrieved with `getLatestBuyerResponse()`

respondChallenge(bytes32).notice: Send a response to the challenge

submitCommitment(bytes[2],uint256,uint25.notice: Submit the data necessary for verification in the case where      m + 1 < i <= n

submitCommitmentLeft(bytes[2],uint256,ui.notice: Submit the data necessary for verification in the case where      i == m + 1

submitCommitmentRight(bytes32[][]).notice: Submit the data necessary for verification in the case where      i == n + 1

timeoutHasPassed().notice: Tells whether the timeout has passed and if a cancellation      or completion can be requested
